# Provider Pattern — obm_gen_with_ai

> Variables: See `_project_config.mdc`. Key values: `{{PROVIDER_BASE}}`, `{{STATE_TYPE}}`, `{{STATE_VALUES}}`, `{{M_SHOW_LOADING}}`, `{{M_SHOW_LOADED}}`, `{{M_SHOW_ERROR}}`, `{{M_SHOW_NO_DATA}}`, `{{M_SET_STATE_NONE}}`, `{{M_SHOW_TOAST}}`, `{{M_SHOW_DIALOG}}`, `{{M_SHOW_PROGRESS}}`, `{{DIO_EXCEPTION}}`, `{{ERROR_MSG}}`.

## State Machine

```
            {{M_SHOW_LOADING}}
   none ──────────────────► loading
                              │
        ┌─────────────────────┼─────────────────────┐
        │                     │                     │
  {{M_SHOW_LOADED}}       {{M_SHOW_ERROR}}       {{M_SHOW_NO_DATA}}
        │                     │                     │
        ▼                     ▼                     ▼
     loaded                error                 noData

   {{M_SET_STATE_NONE}}  ◄── reset back to none
```

`{{PROVIDER_BASE}}` exposes: `currentState`, `{{BASE_PROVIDER_GETTERS}}`, `errorMessage`.

## Provider Template

```dart
class XxxProvider extends {{PROVIDER_BASE}}<XxxService> {
  XxxProvider(XxxService service) : super(service);

  // KHÔNG redeclare {{STATE_TYPE}} — base already has it
  List<XxxModel> items = const [];

  Future<void> fetchItems() async {
    {{M_SHOW_LOADING}};
    try {
      final res = await service.getItems();
      items = res.data ?? const <XxxModel>[];
      items.isEmpty ? {{M_SHOW_NO_DATA}} : {{M_SHOW_LOADED}};
    } on {{DIO_EXCEPTION}} catch (e) {
      errorMessage = {{ERROR_MSG}};
      {{M_SHOW_ERROR}};
    } catch (e) {
      errorMessage = e.toString();
      {{M_SHOW_ERROR}};
    }
  }
}
```

### Multi-operation in same provider

Track each operation with its own `{{STATE_TYPE}}` field:

```dart
{{STATE_TYPE}} detailState = {{G_STATE_NONE}};
XxxModel? detail;

Future<void> loadDetail(String id) async {
  detailState = {{G_STATE_LOADING}};
  notifyListeners();
  try {
    detail = await service.getDetail(id);
    detailState = {{G_STATE_LOADED}};
  } catch (_) {
    detailState = {{G_STATE_ERROR}};
  }
  notifyListeners();
}
```

## Consuming State

### {{CONSUMER_BASE}} (PREFERRED — auto-switches on state)

```dart
class BodyXxxWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return {{CONSUMER_BASE}}<XxxService, XxxProvider>(
      contextParent: context,
      onRepositoryLoading: (_) =>
          const Center(child: CircularProgressIndicator()),
      onRepositorySuccess: (repo) => _buildList(repo as XxxProvider),
      onRepositoryError: (repo) => _buildError(repo as XxxProvider),
      onRepositoryNoData: (repo) => const _EmptyView(),
    );
  }
}
```

`{{CONSUMER_BASE}}` auto-calls `{{PROGRESS_LOAD}}.showProgress/dismissProgress` when `onRepositoryLoading` is not provided.

### {{SELECTOR_BASE}} (ONLY when watching a specific field)

```dart
{{SELECTOR_BASE}}<XxxProvider>(
  selector: (ctx, p) => p.items,
  contextParrent: context,
  onRepository: (ctx, repo) =>
      Text((repo as XxxProvider).items.length.toString()),
)
```

> Note: `{{SELECTOR_BASE}}` has a known issue where `onRepository` always receives `null` as the repository. Use `{{CONSUMER_BASE}}` or `context.select<T, R>()` when repository access is needed.

### Direct read / watch

```dart
context.read<XxxProvider>().fetchItems();         // trigger action
context.watch<XxxProvider>().items;               // listen to all changes
context.select<XxxProvider, int>((p) => p.items.length);  // 1 field
```

## Dialog / Toast / Progress from Provider (eventStream)

```dart
// Dialog
provider.{{M_SHOW_DIALOG}}(
  type: {{DIALOG_TYPE_ENUM}}.warring,       // {{DIALOG_TYPES}}
  title: {{I18N_CLASS}}.notification,
  content: {{I18N_CLASS}}.warningNotConnectInternet,
  onActionCallback: (action) {}, // {{DIALOG_ACTION_ENUM}}.{{DIALOG_ACTION_VALUES}}
);

// Toast
provider.{{M_SHOW_TOAST}}(
  {{I18N_CLASS}}.downloadDataSuccess,
  type: {{TOAST_TYPE_ENUM}}.success,        // {{TOAST_TYPES}}
  duration: const Duration(seconds: 2),
);
```

`{{SCREEN_STATE_BASE}}` init handles eventStream → `DialogHelper`/`ToastHelper`/`ProgressHelper`.

## Loading Counter (global)

`{{LOADING_HUB}}` counts in-flight requests. To disable per-call loading indicator:

```dart
await client.post(
  '/api/xxx',
  data: req,
  options: {{LOADING_SUPPRESS}},
);
```

## Pull-to-Refresh / Load-More

`{{LOAD_MORE_MIXIN}}` (in `base_provider.dart`):

```dart
class XxxProvider extends {{PROVIDER_BASE}}<XxxService> with {{LOAD_MORE_MIXIN}} {
  // page, firstPage, limit=20, refreshControllerDefault are built-in

  Future<void> onLoadMore() async {
    emitLoadComplete(callback: () => page++);
  }
}
```

## DO / DON'T

| DO                                                         | DON'T                                              |
|------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Use `{{M_SHOW_LOADING}}/{{M_SHOW_LOADED}}/{{M_SHOW_ERROR}}/{{M_SHOW_NO_DATA}}` | Directly assign `currentState = {{STATE_TYPE}}.loaded`  |
| Catch `{{DIO_EXCEPTION}}` separately (message already parsed)  | Catch generic `Exception` in provider (masks bugs) |
| Send dialog/toast via `provider.{{M_SHOW_DIALOG}}/{{M_SHOW_TOAST}}` | Call `showDialog`/`fluttertoast` directly from widget |
| `notifyListeners()` after mutating data                    | `setState()` in provider                           |
| Separate `{{STATE_TYPE}}` field per operation              | Reuse `currentState` for multiple independent flows |

## Review Checklist

- [ ] Provider does NOT redeclare `{{STATE_TYPE}} currentState` (base already has it).
- [ ] Every async action goes through `{{M_SHOW_LOADING}}` → `{{M_SHOW_LOADED}}/{{M_SHOW_ERROR}}/{{M_SHOW_NO_DATA}}`.
- [ ] Catches BOTH `{{DIO_EXCEPTION}}` and generic `Exception`.
- [ ] Dialog/Toast/Progress triggered from Provider, not from Widget.
- [ ] No `setState` in provider.
- [ ] No `BuildContext` stored in provider.
- [ ] `mounted` checked after `await` in Widget.
